<AbstractNarration>This award is for the acquisition of a circular dichroism (CD) spectropolarimeter with Peltier temperature control and stopped-flow detection. The instrument will be used for undergraduate research by five investigators and their 20-30 undergraduate students in five different fields of research. &lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Undergraduates will be the primary users of this instrumentation, and they will be trained in theory, data acquisition, and data analysis. This instrumentation will fill a gap in the university's technical capabilities and will improve the exposure of students to fundamental concepts and applications of biomolecular structure. &lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
